metadata.abstract: The document provides detailed information about the Maastricht Radar sectors (EDYY) for VATSIM Germany. It covers the upper airspace above FL245 and includes an overview of the sectors managed by the DeCo and Hanover groups. Each sector is described with its login details, sector indicators, frequencies, callsigns, and specific remarks regarding flight levels. The document emphasizes that the information is for flight simulator use only and not for real-world flight. It also outlines the sector ownership requirements, specifying the approvals needed for controllers to staff various positions within the sectors. The sectors include Holstein, Jever, Delta, Celle, Münster, Ruhr, and Solling, each with defined high and low flight levels. The document is intended for use by VATSIM Germany controllers and provides essential details for managing air traffic within the Maastricht Radar sectors.
